<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,554,653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
This is a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[427,522,554,580]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[540,610,554,581]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2054,2076]" captionText="FIGURE 5. Map of eastern Africa, showing the distribution of Clerodendrum hildebrandtii." pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) based on unmistakable photographs (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1128,554,581]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="5.[136,229,826,848]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,802]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,190,802]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 6. Clerodendrum hildebrandtii, from Ethiopia, Somali Region, 7 km E of Kebri Dehar, Ceelxaar, 29 Sep 2018. A. Leafy shoot, showing calyces and bud. B. Young leafy shoot with more rounded leaves and with open flower and bud. Photographs by Hassan Yusuf Kaariye." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5308339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5308339/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Several shrubs, up to 
<quantity box="[1406,1452,554,581]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" unit="m" value="5.0">5 m</quantity>
tall, were seen in open bushland at or near banks of a water pond and seasonal streams (Hassan Yusuf Kaariye, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
