<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="67" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,967,1317]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vatke" authorityYear="1882" box="[189,504,967,993]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Clerodendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis box="[189,504,967,993]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Clerodendrum hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[848,921,968,994]" name="Kenya" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vatke, W." box="[934,1066,967,993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="507 - 541" refId="ref3481" refString="Vatke, W. (1882) Plantas in itinere africano ab J. M. Hildebrandt collectas determinare pergit. Linnaea 43: 507 - 541. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 10891  page / 530 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1882">Vatke 1882</bibRefCitation>
), but is known also from 
<collectingCountry box="[1344,1448,967,993]" name="Tanzania" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[241,333,1003,1029]" name="Somalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Somalia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B." box="[349,529,1003,1029]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref3532" refString="Verdcourt, B. (1992) Verbenaceae. In: Polhill, R. M. (Ed.) Flora of tropical East Africa. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam / Brookfield, pp. 1 - 155." type="book chapter" year="1992">Verdcourt 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Thulin, M." box="[541,699,1003,1030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="313 - 315" refId="ref3441" refString="Thulin, M. (2006 b) Clerodendrum. In: Thulin, M. (Ed.) Flora of Somalia, vol. 3. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 313 - 315." type="book chapter" year="2006">Thulin 2006b</bibRefCitation>
), and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[873,1021,1003,1029]" name="Mozambique" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes, R." box="[1037,1223,1003,1030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="61 - 153" refId="ref2568" refString="Fernandes, R. (2005) Lamiaceae (subfams. Viticoideae and Ajugoideae). In: Pope, G. V. &amp; Martins, E. S. (Eds.) Flora Zambesiaca, vol. 8 (7). Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 61 - 153." type="book chapter" year="2005">Fernandes 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Plants in 
<collectingCountry box="[1351,1452,1003,1029]" name="Tanzania" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
with pubescent young stems and leaves have been described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Verdcourt (1992: 110" authorityName="Verdcourt" authorityYear="1992" box="[845,1447,1039,1066]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Clerodendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="hildebrandtii" variety="puberulum">
<emphasis box="[845,1023,1039,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">C. hildebrandtii</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1078,1199,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">puberulum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B." box="[1206,1447,1039,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref3532" refString="Verdcourt, B. (1992) Verbenaceae. In: Polhill, R. M. (Ed.) Flora of tropical East Africa. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam / Brookfield, pp. 1 - 155." type="book chapter" year="1992">Verdcourt (1992: 110</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; as “ 
<emphasis box="[179,280,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">puberula</emphasis>
”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,967,1317]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[224,297,1112,1138]" name="Kenya" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[360,461,1111,1137]" name="Tanzania" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vatke" authorityYear="1882" box="[472,655,1111,1138]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Clerodendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis box="[472,655,1111,1138]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">C. hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from various 
<typeStatus box="[944,1003,1112,1138]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">types</typeStatus>
of bushland and wooded grassland at elevations up to 
<quantity box="[323,395,1147,1174]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="900.0">900 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B." box="[410,591,1147,1173]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref3532" refString="Verdcourt, B. (1992) Verbenaceae. In: Polhill, R. M. (Ed.) Flora of tropical East Africa. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam / Brookfield, pp. 1 - 155." type="book chapter" year="1992">Verdcourt 1992</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[642,734,1147,1173]" name="Somalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Somalia</collectingCountry>
it is known from bushland and woodland on sandy or silty soil at elevations up to 
<quantity box="[356,429,1183,1210]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="230.0">230 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thulin, M." box="[445,604,1183,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="313 - 315" refId="ref3441" refString="Thulin, M. (2006 b) Clerodendrum. In: Thulin, M. (Ed.) Flora of Somalia, vol. 3. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 313 - 315." type="book chapter" year="2006">Thulin 2006b</bibRefCitation>
), whereas in 
<collectingCountry box="[757,905,1183,1209]" name="Mozambique" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
it occurs in wooded grassland and bushland on sandy periodically inundated soils at elevations up to about 
<quantity box="[821,893,1219,1246]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes, R." box="[909,1096,1219,1246]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="61 - 153" refId="ref2568" refString="Fernandes, R. (2005) Lamiaceae (subfams. Viticoideae and Ajugoideae). In: Pope, G. V. &amp; Martins, E. S. (Eds.) Flora Zambesiaca, vol. 8 (7). Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 61 - 153." type="book chapter" year="2005">Fernandes 2005</bibRefCitation>
). The map in 
<figureCitation box="[1255,1322,1219,1245]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="5.[136,229,826,848]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,802]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,190,802]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 6. Clerodendrum hildebrandtii, from Ethiopia, Somali Region, 7 km E of Kebri Dehar, Ceelxaar, 29 Sep 2018. A. Leafy shoot, showing calyces and bud. B. Young leafy shoot with more rounded leaves and with open flower and bud. Photographs by Hassan Yusuf Kaariye." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5308339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5308339/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
shows that the Ethiopian record is some 
<quantity box="[463,547,1255,1282]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="km" value="450.0">450 km</quantity>
from the nearest localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[879,971,1255,1281]" name="Somalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Somalia</collectingCountry>
and is the northernmost one known for the species.
</paragraph>
